										<footer class="article-contributor contributors">
									

<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Poe Ballantine</span></strong> is the author of the true-crime book <em>Love and Terror on the Howling Plains of Nowhere</em>, to be published in 2012, and the subject of the forthcoming documentary <em>Poe Ballantine, A Writer in America</em>. Because the rural school in Dawes County, Nebraska, where he worked as a custodian has been closed, he is now considering a job in the uranium fields twenty miles west, both for the money and because he&rsquo;s always liked yellow cake.</p><a href="/contributors/poe-ballantine" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

