			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="652">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I was moved by Poe Ballantine&rsquo;s visceral and candid depiction of the hardships of his best friend Cliff and his own experience raising his son, Tom [&ldquo;<a href="/article/4555">Guidelines for Mountain-Lion Safety</a>,&rdquo; July 2011]. His story is one of overcoming adversity and social abandonment and an unquenchable thirst for belonging. The advice Ballantine gave to his son, for dealing with bullies the same way one should deal with a mountain lion, was brilliant. In a world filled with predators and prey, it is essential to stand tall and hold your ground.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Stephen Underwood<br>Plainville, Connecticut</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="653">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>On a recent backpacking trip, I missed seeing a mountain lion by seconds. In the meantime I&rsquo;ll settle for Poe Ballantine&rsquo;s &ldquo;Guidelines for Mountain-Lion Safety.&rdquo; The mountain lion usually attacks in one leap and a bound, the same way Ballantine writes. It uses its long tail as a rudder to finely adjust its movement; Ballantine uses his life&rsquo;s experience to similar ruthless effectiveness.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">John W. Mitchell<br>Fort Collins, Colorado</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

				<div class="text-center">
			<button class="b b-1 xsmall js-b-readmore-correspondence" data-collapsible="#article-correspondences" data-label="Read More Letters">Read More Letters</button>
		</div>
			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

